# .hmaignore -- opena2a-cli HackMyAgent self-scan suppressions.
#
# Every entry below was triaged as a FALSE POSITIVE on this tool's own code in
# issue #188 (github.com/opena2a-org/opena2a/issues/188). No genuine finding is
# suppressed. Do NOT add a real finding here; fix real findings in source.
#
# Format (per HMA scanner): lines starting with `#` are comments; bare lines are
# path prefixes (relative to the scan target, e.g. `hackmyagent secure packages/cli`);
# lines starting with `!` are check IDs suppressed across the scan.

# --- Non-shipped dev/test code (npm `files` ships dist/ + README only) ---
# Test fixtures intentionally embed the exact threat patterns the scanners look
# for (eval() blocks, exec() calls) as INPUT, to assert detection fires. The
# patterns are string literals fed to scanSkillFile/scanners, never executed.
# Clears NEMO-009 (eval fixture) and the NEMO-008 test pairing.
__tests__
# Release-smoke harness spreads process.env into a child it fully controls to
# run the deterministic corpus locally. Not shipped. Clears one NEMO-007.
scripts

# --- Subprocess launchers: full env passthrough is by design ---
# The adapters spawn bundled OpenA2A tools, the user's own docker/python image,
# or the agent under the user's control. The child is trusted and needs the
# inherited environment (PATH, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, registry bearer tokens) to
# run; narrowing to PATH+NODE_ENV would break delegation. Not an env leak to an
# adversary. Clears the adapters' NEMO-007.
src/adapters
# shield/llm-backend spawns the local `claude` CLI (haiku, single turn) for
# optional defense-in-depth semantic analysis; it needs the inherited env to
# authenticate. Same by-design rationale. Clears NEMO-007 here.
src/shield/llm-backend.ts

# --- File-scoped suppressions (heuristics that misfire on these files) ---
# Scoped to the exact FP files rather than a project-wide `!CHECKID`, so a
# genuine future NEMO-008/MEM-006 elsewhere in the tool still surfaces.
#
# NEMO-008 (TOCTOU) pairs a "verify"-like token in one file with an exec in an
# UNRELATED file. The token here is the JSDoc line "selfcheck: Run integrity
# checks" in shield.ts; opena2a-cli never verifies-then-executes the same
# artifact (`guard` hashes files for tamper REPORTING and never runs them).
src/commands/shield.ts
# MEM-006 ("memory store without input sanitization") matches `.push()` into the
# transient in-memory report arrays `tampered` (guard-snapshots.ts) and `diffs`
# (guard.ts). Those arrays are built per-invocation purely for stdout rendering;
# they are never persisted and never sent to an LLM, and the only input field is
# a filePath drawn from the tool's own signature store. opena2a-cli has no
# LLM-memory persistence layer for this check to protect.
src/commands/guard.ts
src/commands/guard-snapshots.ts
